4, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"score\": 0.5976080028338996, \"rank\": 0.5825706925136351, \"text\": \"Luo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\"}, {\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shifang\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shifang\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Making her Olympic debut in Paris, Luo set three new Olympic records by lifting 107 kg in the snatch and 134 kg in the clean and jerk, achieving a winning total of 241 kg.\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990182005, \"rank\": 9.819334046526542e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"score\": 0.5976080028338996, \"rank\": 0.5825706925136351, \"text\": \"Luo\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Luo_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's canoe double 500 meter event, China's Liu Hao and Ji Bowen won gold with a time of 1:39.48, finishing ahead of Italy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Gabriele Casadei and Carlo Tacchini, who took silver, and Spain\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Joan Antoni Moreno and Diego Dominguez, who earned bronze.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 1092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 875, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r